The presence of the corresponding fluoroscopy and CT\narteries in the AHA 17-segment model agreed well with a Kappa value of 0.91(95%\nCI: 0.89-0.93) for LCA and 0.80(CI: 0.67-0.92) for RCA. Conclusions. Our fusion\napproach is technically accurate to assist PCI decision-making and is\nclinically feasible to be used in the catheterization laboratory. There is an\nopportunity to improve the decision-making and outcomes of PCI in stable CAD.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Jun 2020 02:06:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-15"}
