{"id":"2006.07170","submitter":"Tiberiu Harko","authors":"Tiberiu Harko, Man Kwong Mak","title":"A simple computational approach to the Susceptible-Infected-Recovered\n  (SIR) epidemic model via the Laplace-Adomian Decomposition Method","comments":"9 pages, 2 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"q-bio.PE q-bio.QM","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The Susceptible-Infected-Recovered (SIR) epidemic model is extensively used\nfor the study of the spread of infectious diseases. Even that the exact\nsolution of the model can be obtained in an exact parametric form, in order to\nperform the comparison with the epidemiological data a simple but highly\naccurate representation of the time evolution of the SIR compartments would be\nvery useful. In the present paper we obtain a series representation of the\nsolution of the SIR model by using the Laplace-Adomian Decomposition Method to\nsolve the basic evolution equation of the model. The solutions are expressed in\nthe form of infinite series. The series representations of the time evolution\nof the SIR compartments are compared with the exact numerical solutions of the\nmodel. We find that there is a good agreement between the Laplace-Adomian\nsemianalytical solutions containing only three terms, and the numerical\nresults.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Jun 2020 13:26:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 16 Jun 2020 06:08:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-17"}
